cs.SI, cs.CY, cs.SOC, cs.IR, cs.CL 

This paper analyzes the use of sentiment in social media news channels, which involves natural language processing and social media analysis. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Additionally, the paper involves data analysis and machine learning techniques, which could fall under cs.CY (Computers and Society) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval). The paper also discusses the differences in the ways news channels cover the news, which could be related to cs.SOC (Social and Behavioral Sciences) and cs.CL (Computation and Language).
